dc:description: Bronze Sestertius with head of Augustus. Diam. 0.035 m, Wt. 24.13 g. Mint: Lugdunum (Lyons). Obv.: Laureate head of Augustus facing right, beaded frame, DIVI F PATER PATRIAE CAESAR AVGVSTVS. Rev.: Altar of Rome and Augustus at Lugdunum. Front elevation, decorated with corona civica between laurels, flanked by nude male figures. Framed by winged Victories on columns facing each other, holding coronas, ROM ET AVG below. Very worn. Bronze (Rocks, Paper, Memory; Larson).
